---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`Churn (Customer & Revenue) | ${siteName}`}
  description="Churn definition, logo churn vs revenue churn, and how to use churn in LTV and pricing models."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Churn</h1>
    <p>Churn measures how much customer count or revenue you lose over time. Itâ€™s a core driver of SaaS growth and LTV.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>Two common definitions</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Customer (logo) churn</strong>: % of customers who cancel in a period.</li>
        <li><strong>Revenue churn</strong>: % of recurring revenue lost in a period (can be gross or net of expansion).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Why churn matters for pricing</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Price increases can improve revenue but may raise churn; you need a break-even point.</li>
        <li>Annual prepay can reduce churn (commitment) but changes cash timing and discounting decisions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/churn-impact-calculator/">Churn impact calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/pricing-increase-impact-calculator/">Pricing increase impact calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/ltv-calculator/">LTV calculator</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/ltv/">LTV</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/annual-prepay-discount/">Annual discount</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

